boostsOf(uint256).details: A basic revnet consists of cycles defined by scheduled boost periods. The only changes between them are in their reserved rate.

params._controller: The controller that revnets are made from.

params._boostOperator: The address that will receive the token premint and initial boost, and who is allowed to change the boost recipients. Only the boost operator can replace itself after deployment.
params._buybackHookSetupData: Data used for setting up the buyback hook to use when determining the best price for new participants.
params._name: The name of the ERC-20 token being create for the revnet.
params._revnetData: The data needed to deploy a basic revnet.
params._symbol: The symbol of the ERC-20 token being created for the revnet.
params._terminals: The terminals that the network uses to accept payments through.

returns.revnetId: The ID of the newly created revnet.
